# 🎤 Interviewer

> You are given an employee DataFrame with the following columns:
>
> `emp_id`, `name`, `department`, `salary`, `city`
>
> Some records contain **NULL** values.
>
> Write PySpark code to perform the following tasks:
>
> 1. Display all employees whose **salary is NULL**.
> 2. Replace all **NULL salary values with `0`**.
> 3. Replace all **NULL city values with `"Unknown"`**.
> 4. Remove all rows where **department is NULL**.
>
> Write clean, production-ready PySpark code.

---

## 📊 Dataset

| emp_id | name  | department | salary | city      |
| ------ | ----- | ---------- | ------ | --------- |
| 101    | John  | IT         | 60000  | Mumbai    |
| 102    | David | HR         | NULL   | Delhi     |
| 103    | Alice | IT         | 70000  | NULL      |
| 104    | Bob   | NULL       | 55000  | Hyderabad |
